and media company in bankruptcy, settled a dispute with a panel
of its unsecured creditors by offering bondholders
$420 million, the company said.  The settlement comes as Tribune continues to try to
negotiate an end to a fight among its creditors, who are divided
over the publisherâ€™s plan to exit bankruptcy.  The case is In re Tribune Co., 08-13141, U.S. Bankruptcy
